<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F1C9C353FE51315E" authority="Weise 1923: 141" authorityName="Weise" authorityPageNumber="141" authorityYear="1923" box="[151,444,1638,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Amidellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32B3EAD4FFD4EB15F1C9C353FF11315E" box="[151,252,1638,1660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Amidellus</emphasis>
Weise 1923: 141
</taxonomicName>
. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F33CC352FC32315E" authority="Blackburn, 1895" authorityName="Blackburn" authorityYear="1895" box="[610,991,1638,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Scymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ementitor">
<emphasis id="32B3EAD4FFD4EB15F33CC352FCCB315F" box="[610,806,1639,1661]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Scymnus ementitor</emphasis>
Blackburn, 1895
</taxonomicName>
by original designation. Synonymized by 
<treatmentCitation id="816610D7FFD4EB15F199C3B0FE6D31B9" author="" box="[199,384,1669,1691]" page="87" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<bibRefCitation id="64564B37FFD4EB15F199C3B0FEB331B9" box="[199,350,1669,1691]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4962" refString="Slipinski, A. (2007) Australian Ladybird Beetles (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae): Their Biology and Classification. Australian Biological Resources Study, Canberra, ACT, 288 pp." type="book">Ślipiński 2007</bibRefCitation>
: 87
</treatmentCitation>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="64564B37FFD4EB15F0E8C3B0FDA031B9" box="[438,589,1669,1691]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4240" refString="Gordon, R. D. (1976) The Scymnini of the United States and Canada: Key to genera and revision of Scymnus, Nephus and Diomus. Bulletin of the Buffalo Society of Natural Sciences, 28, 1 - 362." type="journal article">Gordon (1976)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="64564B37FFD4EB15F320C3B3FC8531B9" box="[638,872,1669,1691]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4814" refString="Pang, X. F. &amp; Gordon, R. D. (1986) The Scymnini (Coleoptera: Coccinellidae) of China. The Coleopterists Bulletin, 40, 157 - 199." type="journal article">Pang &amp; Gordon (1986)</bibRefCitation>
for a more complete bibliography).
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007836C6FFD4EB15F1C9C3FDFE0E30FF" blockId="1.[151,1437,1735,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F1C9C3FDFF0331FD" authorityName=": Weise" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,238,1736,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Diomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32B3EAD4FFD4EB15F1C9C3FDFF0331FD" box="[151,238,1736,1759]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Diomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the most speciose genus in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F3F4C3F2FCEA31C2" authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1999" box="[682,775,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Diomini">Diomini</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="64564B37FFD4EB15F251C3F2FC4231C2" box="[783,943,1735,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4197" refString="Gordon, R. (1999) South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part VI: A systematic revision of the South American Diomini, new tribe (Scymninae). Annales Zoologici, Warsaw, 49, 1 - 219." type="journal article">Gordon, 1999</bibRefCitation>
, and possibly the largest genus in the entire family 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F1B8C3D9FDC63026" authority="Latreille, 1807" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1807" box="[230,555,1772,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Coccinellidae Latreille, 1807</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="64564B37FFD4EB15F367C3D9FCD73026" box="[569,826,1772,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4716" refString="Pang, H. &amp; Slipinski, A. (2009) Revision of the Australian Coccinellidae (Coleoptera). Genus Diomus Mulsant. Part 1. Annales Zoologici, 59, 641 - 698. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 000345409 x 485008" type="journal article">Pang &amp; Ślipiński 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="64564B37FFD4EB15F21BC3D9FC6F3026" box="[837,898,1772,1796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4765" refString="Pang, H. &amp; Slipinski, A. (2010) Revision of the Australian Coccinellidae (Coleoptera). Genus Diomus Mulsant. Part 2. Annales Zoologici, 60, 493 - 545. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 000345410 X 550382" type="journal article">2010</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F2CDC3D8FC073026" authorityName=": Weise" authorityYear="1895" box="[915,1002,1773,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Diomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32B3EAD4FFD4EB15F2CDC3D8FC073026" box="[915,1002,1773,1796]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Diomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally placed as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F1C9C225FE55300A" authority="Kugellan, 1794" authorityName="Kugellan" authorityYear="1794" box="[151,440,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Scymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32B3EAD4FFD4EB15F1C9C225FF143005" box="[151,249,1808,1831]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Scymnus</emphasis>
Kugellan, 1794
</taxonomicName>
, and classified, until recent times, in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F2BFC23AFBA0300A" box="[993,1101,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scymnini">Scymnini</taxonomicName>
Mulsant, 1846 along with a miscellaneous assortment of other small pubescent lady beetles. 
<bibRefCitation id="64564B37FFD4EB15F227C201FBCF306E" box="[889,1058,1844,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref4197" refString="Gordon, R. (1999) South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part VI: A systematic revision of the South American Diomini, new tribe (Scymninae). Annales Zoologici, Warsaw, 49, 1 - 219." type="journal article">Gordon (1999)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F5F1C200FAEB306E" authorityName=": Weise" authorityYear="1895" box="[1199,1286,1845,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Diomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32B3EAD4FFD4EB15F5F1C200FAEB306E" box="[1199,1286,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">Diomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and allies as deserving of their own tribe 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F084C262FDD73052" authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1999" box="[474,570,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Diomini">Diomini</taxonomicName>
, distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F3BEC262FCA33052" box="[736,846,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scymnini">Scymnini</taxonomicName>
, but unfortunately his circumscription of the former included some genera belonging to another tribe—Selvadiini Gordon, 1985 (
<bibRefCitation id="64564B37FFD4EB15F546C249FE8E309A" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" refId="ref5160" refString="Vandenberg, N. J. (2002) Coccinellidae Latreille, 1807. In: Arnett, R. &amp; Thomas, M. (Eds.), American Beetles. Vol. 2. Polyphaga: Scarabaeoidea through Curculionoidea. CRC Press, Boca Raton, FL, pp. 371 - 389." type="book chapter">Vandenberg 2002; Vandenberg &amp; Hanson in review</bibRefCitation>
). A re-circumscription and review of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C74D45FFD4EB15F254C2AAFC8A309A" authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1999" box="[778,871,1951,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Diomini">Diomini</taxonomicName>
is detailed in Vandenberg and Hanson (in review) and will not be repeated here.
</paragraph>
